    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about needing an escrow account for this house i'm looking at in toronto. i've never bought a place before so i'm kinda lost. can u explain what escrow actually is and why it's even used in the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral third-party account where funds and documents are held by a lender or title company until all conditions of the purchase are met. It ensures that neither the buyer nor the seller can be defrauded, as the money only transfers to the seller once the title is cleared and the deed is signed. In Toronto, this is standard practice to protect both parties during the closing process, especially when dealing with large sums and complex regulations. You should discuss the escrow terms with your realtor and lawyer to understand any specific fees or timelines involved for your property.",
