      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right to be cautious; the \"middle ground\" does sound a bit odd at first glance, but it is actually a critical safety mechanism designed specifically to prevent exactly the risks you are worried about. The money doesn't just sit there aimlessly; it is placed in a legally regulated account managed by a licensed escrow agent who acts as a strict accountant and enforcer of the contract terms. If the seller tries to take the money early or before the deeds are transferred, the escrow agent will legally freeze the funds and refuse to release them, ensuring the transaction only completes when every single condition of the sale is perfectly satisfied.",
